<div class='mailer__content'>
  <p class='govuk-body'>Dear <%= @user.first_name %>,</p>

  <p class='govuk-body'>Congratulations on your professional development progress! You have now completed the required hours of CPD to unlock the Key Stage 3 and GCSE Computer Science subject knowledge certificate test.</p>

  <p class='govuk-body'>Take the test now (approximately 30 minutes) and obtain your accredited certificate.</p>

  <p class='govuk-body'>
    <%= link_to 'Take the test', cs_accelerator_url, class: 'govuk-button button' %>
  </p>

  <p class='govuk-body'><strong>How does it work?</strong></p>

    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list">
    <li>The test is timed and multiple choice</li>
    <li>It should be taken under exam conditions, and you'll need to provide contact details of a member of your leadership team who can confirm this</li>
  </ul>

  <p class='govuk-body'><strong>Need more support?</strong></p>

  <p class="govuk-body">Take our  <%= link_to 'mock test', 'https://www.classmarker.com/online-test/start/?quiz=gq36013dee29b07b', class: 'ncce-link' %> to assess your subject knowledge and identify any areas from the curriculum where you need further support. We also have resources to help you prepare for your test, including:</p>
  <ul>

    <li><%= link_to 'Preparing to take the test (short course)', course_url(id: 'CP350', name: 'preparing-to-take-the-csa-test-short-course'), class: 'ncce-link' %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'Certificate handbook', 'https://ncce.io/csa-handbook', class: 'ncce-link' %></li>
  </ul>

  <p class='govuk-body'>We also recommend you complete more courses to ensure you possess well-rounded subject knowledge before attempting to take the test.</p>

  <p class='govuk-body'><strong>Ready to take the test?</strong></p>

  <p class='govuk-body'>Depending on your starting point, you may also benefit from engaging in CPD from other areas of computer science. Explore the full range of CPD available to you on <%= link_to 'our courses page', courses_url %>.</p>

  <p class='govuk-body'>Good luck!</p>
</div>
